{
  "texts": [
    "Writing ρ ′′ = Tr H C ′ {ρ} for the restriction of ρ to the annular region C ′′, we immediately obtain that Tr H C ′′ {ρ ′′ t S (P X)} = 1.",
    "It follows that ρ ′′ belongs to D C ′′ (P X, id), where the first slot corresponds to the boundary component S and the second slot corresponds to the boundary component Ŝ′.",
    "By Proposition 4.6, in fact ρ ′′ ∈ D C ′′ (P X, P X), meaning that Tr H C ′′ {ρ ′′ t Ŝ′ (P X)} = 1.Using (34), and the fact that (P X) op = P X for any minimal central projector P X of a Tube algebra, we getTr H C ′ {ρ ′ t S ′ (P X)} = Tr H C {ρ B C t S ′ (P X)} = Tr H C {ρ B C t op Ŝ′ (P X)} = Tr H C {ρ B C t Ŝ′ (P X)} = Tr H C ′′ {ρ ′′ t Ŝ′ (P X)} = 1as desired.",
    "□ Gluing along intervalsA dual path I = {f i } l i=1 is a sequence of faces such that f i neighbours f i+1 for all i = 1, • • •, l-1.",
    "This dual path is self-avoiding if all the f i are distinct."
  ]
}